# Merge strategy for the repo's append-only prose + structured tracking files.
#
# NONE of these use `merge=union` anymore. Union merge takes all lines from all branches, which
# looked safe for "prose that only ever grows" (CHANGELOG entries, per-doc changelog footers) — but
# across a SQUASH-divergent or cross-branch promotion (e.g. dev → integration → main, where main's
# history is rewritten by squash-landing) it silently appends BOTH sides of a touched block, producing
# DUPLICATE entries: duplicate CHANGELOG headings (markdownlint MD024) and duplicate ADR/RFC changelog
# bullets. Those are syntactically valid but semantically broken, and they slip through unless caught
# by a lint gate (CLAUDE.md swarm mitigation #2 — originally applied to idmap.tsv / issues.yaml; now
# extended to the prose files for the same reason).
#
# All of these therefore use the default 3-way merge: a genuine collision surfaces as an EXPLICIT
# conflict to reconcile by hand — never a silent duplicate (G2). These files are append-only by
# discipline (new entry at the top / a new dated bullet), so real conflicts are rare and, when they
# happen, are exactly what a human should see.
#
#   CHANGELOG.md, docs/notes/*.md, docs/rfcs/*.md, docs/adr/*.md  — default 3-way merge (was union)
#   tools/github/idmap.tsv, tools/github/issues.yaml             — default 3-way merge (since #397)
#
# (Intentionally no `merge=union` lines here. Do not re-add them without a decision — they trade a
# rare explicit conflict for a silent, lint-only-detectable duplicate.)

# GitHub Linguist repo-stat classification (M-697; tools/grammar/DISTRIBUTION.md §a/§e).
#
# WHY: GitHub's repo-language bar (and `git diff`/PR line-stat totals) is driven by Linguist's
# generated/vendored/binary/documentation classification. Two honesty concerns this block covers
# (transparency rule, house rules #1/#2):
#
#   1. Repo-stat honesty: machine-derived artifacts (regenerated by `tools/grammar/generate.py` /
#      `just docs-index` / `vsce package`, never hand-edited) should not inflate the repo's
#      "written by hand" language stats or dominate PR diffs, and the grammar conformance fixture
#      corpus (pinned accept/reject cases, not hand-authored "Mycelium usage") should not either.
#      `linguist-generated=true` / `linguist-vendored=true` only change how GitHub *counts* a path
#      for the language bar and default diff collapsing — they change nothing about what is
#      committed, reviewed, or tested.
#   2. FORBIDDEN PATTERN — do not map `.myc` to an existing language via `linguist-language=`.
#      GitHub currently shows `.myc` as "Other" because Linguist has no entry for Mycelium yet.
#      A line like `*.myc linguist-language=Rust` (or any other existing language) would make the
#      language bar LIE by mislabeling Mycelium source as a language it isn't — exactly the kind of
#      no-EXPLAIN misrepresentation the transparency rule forbids (G2/VR-5), and it would also
#      block Linguist's own `.myc` detection once a real grammar is registered. The only honest way
#      to make "Mycelium" appear in the language bar is the real Linguist grammar submission gated
#      in `tools/grammar/DISTRIBUTION.md` §e (a `github-linguist/linguist` PR via `script/add-grammar`
#      + `script/update-ids`) — never a same-repo attribute shortcut. Do not add a
#      `linguist-language=` line for `*.myc` in this file.

# Generated artifacts — excluded from the language bar + collapsed in diffs by default; still
# committed, reviewed, and drift-gated (`just drift-check`) as normal.
docs/api-index/** linguist-generated
tools/grammar/mycelium.tmLanguage.json linguist-generated
tools/grammar/keywords.json linguist-generated
tools/grammar/tree-sitter-mycelium/grammar.js linguist-generated
tools/grammar/tree-sitter-mycelium/queries/highlights.scm linguist-generated
tools/grammar/tree-sitter-mycelium/src/** linguist-generated
editors/vscode/syntaxes/mycelium.tmLanguage.json linguist-generated

# Packaged binary artifact (the VS Code/Cursor extension package) — never text-diffed.
*.vsix binary

# Vendored test fixtures — the grammar conformance corpus (pinned accept/reject `.myc` cases),
# not hand-authored language usage.
docs/spec/grammar/conformance/** linguist-vendored
